@NODE Introduction "RB2Exe Guide    Copyright © 2000 by Andreas Falkenhahn"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

    RB2Exe is THE add-on you always wanted for Rainboot2. RB2Exe converts
    Rainboot configurations into fully stand alone executables. All the
    data of the configuration is linked to one executable, which will run
    on every Amiga system running at least OS2.04. So you can create now
    your own demonstrations and shows with Rainboot (and distribute them
    then!).

    RB2Exe is a Shareware program. The executables that are generated by
    the Shareware version of RB2Exe are crippled, and must not be spread.
    To register RB2Exe, have a look at @{"this section" link Registration}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "RB2Exe Guide    Copyright © 2000 by Andreas Falkenhahn"
@{b}Requirements@{ub}

    RB2Exe requires at least OS3.0. However, the generated executables will
    work on any Amiga with OS2.04.
    
    RB2Exe uses guigfx.library and render.library by Timm S. Müller. They
    are included in generic versions in this archive. You can get the
    full distribution archive on Aminet.

    The generated executable will need iff.library by Christian A. Weber.
    Optionally the executable will also need ptreplay.library, player61.library,
    thxplay.library and identify.library by Richard Körber. This depends
    on the commands used in the Rainboot configuration.

    To use the install-script you need the NewInstaller program which is
    available on Aminet (util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "RB2Exe Guide    Copyright © 2000 by Andreas Falkenhahn"
@{b}Installation@{ub}

    To install RB2Exe just click on the install icon and follow the
    instructions.

    Please note: The installation needs NewInstaller to function. Please
    download NewInstaller from http://airsoft.home.pages.de/ or from Aminet
    (util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "RB2Exe Guide    Copyright © 2000 by Andreas Falkenhahn"
@{b}Using RB2Exe@{ub}

    The usage of RB2Exe is pretty simple. The GUI has a status bar
    that displays information about the buttons, when the mouse is
    over them. Anyway, here's a description of each button's function:

    Convert: If you click this button, you're prompted to select a
             configuration that shall be converted into an executable.
             You also have to select the destination file and the
             graphics mode, the executable shall use (AGA/RTG/Ask user).

    Help: Displays this documentation.
  
    About: Displays some information about the program.

    Quit: Exits RB2Exe.
  
    
    All those functions can also be selected in the menu. One thing
    can only be selected in the menu: CreateIcon. If you turn this item
    on, the generated executable will get an icon, otherwise it won't
    get one.

@ENDNODE

